  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-6 clean)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Seven factors are assessed with achieved levels meeting or exceeding required levels. Six factors are marked not-applicable with documented rationale explaining why each does not apply to this CFD-based hemolysis prediction context. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. Decision: Accepted on the basis of all assessed factors meeting their required credibility levels.",
